HEADWORD: Remanet
<hw>Rem"a*net</hw> <pr>(-n?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., it
remains.]</ety> <fld>(Legal Practice)</fld> <def>A case for trial which
can not be tried during the term; a postponed case.</def>
